# class: architecture-fr
# schema: id | title | summary | source
# source: docs/architecture.md
# recipe: builtin:architecture

FR-01 | <title> | <one-line statement of the requirement> | @docs/architecture.md#fr-01
FR-02 | <title> | <one-line statement of the requirement> | @docs/architecture.md#fr-02

# Recipe: every Functional Requirement in the source architecture doc gets one row.
# Body NOT copied — summary is one line. Roles read source-doc section only when verbatim wording is needed.
# Lossless rule: every FR named in the source has an entry.
# NFR table → constraints.yaml (categorized) instead of a flat list, because NFRs carry budgets + per-role-impact.
